response.original_title: We Got Moves You Ain’t Even Heard Of (Part One)
response.overview: Comments humorously on sexual identity, butch/femme roles, and Hollywood’s Orientalism by re-casting the filmmaker as the lead in The Karate Kid and its sequels of the 1980s, and, alternately, by re-imagining teen idol Ralph Macchio as a lesbian icon. -Eve Oishi, "Bad Asians, the Sequel: Continuing Trends in Queer API Film and Video"
